div.p:
“Let’s go to Atlantis and take the learned gentleman with us,” said Anthea;
                    “he’ll think it’s a dream, afterwards, but it’ll certainly be a change of
                    scene.”

“Then I advise you to get on to the highest ground you can find. I remember
                    hearing something about a flood here. Look here, you”—it turned to Anthea;
                    “let’s get home. The prospect’s too wet for my whiskers.”

The priest led the children up the steps till they all stood before the throne;
                    and then, suddenly, he fell on his face with hands outstretched. The others did
                    the same, Anthea falling very carefully because of the Psammead.
